cbStatNumBytesTXed.name: cbStatNumBytesTXed
cbStatNumBytesTXed.description: Number of bytes transmitted since last statistics reset.

cbStatNumOfPackets.name: cbStatNumOfPackets
cbStatNumOfPackets.description: Number of data packets transmitted since last statistics reset.

cbStatAvrPktSize.name: cbStatAvrPktSize
cbStatAvrPktSize.description: Average packet size since last statistics reset.

cbStatAvrBytesPerSec.name: cbStatAvrBytesPerSec
cbStatAvrBytesPerSec.description: Average speed in bytes per second since last statistics reset.

cbStatNumPacketDiscarded.name: cbStatNumPacketDiscarded
cbStatNumPacketDiscarded.description: Number of data packets that were discarded since last statistics reset.

cbStatNumNMSFrames.name: cbStatNumNMSFrames
cbStatNumNMSFrames.description: Number of NMS packets received since last statistics reset.

cbStatReset.name: cbStatReset
cbStatReset.description: Set to cbTrue in order to reset the general statistics values (either in active or non-active mode).

cbStatNumClients.name: cbStatNumClients
cbStatNumClients.description: Number of clients currently connected to the Gateway. It is not part of the General Statistics since the cbStatReset does not change its value.

cbClientIP.name: cbClientIP
cbClientIP.description: The IP address of the client. The rest of the params in cbStatClient reffers to this IP. In order to get a statistics on a single clients, set cbClientIP to the IP of the desired client and get the results under cbClientStatistics. Continuously get operations of the rest of the params will give the updated statistics values without a need to set cbClientIP again and again.

cbClNumSeconds.name: cbClNumSeconds
cbClNumSeconds.description: The number of seconds since the client statistics are active. The statistics values are reset automaticaly by the gateway (as well as by setting cbClReset) according to the value of cbFreqClientsInfoReset.

cbClNumKBytes.name: cbClNumKBytes
cbClNumKBytes.description: Number of bytes transmitted to IP==cbClientIP in the last cbClNumSeconds seconds.

cbClNumPackets.name: cbClNumPackets
cbClNumPackets.description: Number of packets transmitted to IP==cbClientIP in the last cbClNumSeconds seconds.

cbClAvrBytesPerSecond.name: cbClAvrBytesPerSecond
cbClAvrBytesPerSecond.description: Average transfer rate in bytes per second for this client.

cbClNumPacketsDiscarded.name: cbClNumPacketsDiscarded
cbClNumPacketsDiscarded.description: Number of packets discarded to IP==cbClientIP in the last cbClNumSeconds seconds.

cbClStatReset.name: cbClStatReset
cbClStatReset.description: Set ot non-zero - Reset the statistics values for the client cbClientIP.

cbClEncrEnbled.name: cbClEncrEnbled
cbClEncrEnbled.description: If this variable is True then the user desire encryption. This value may not changed and it is NOT changed by setting cbClStatReset.

cbClTable.name: cbClTable
cbClTable.description: This table contains updated statistics of all clients known to the gateway.

cbClTableTotalPackets.name: cbClTableTotalPackets
cbClTableTotalPackets.description: Total Packets transmitted to this client.

cbClTablePacketsDiscr.name: cbClTablePacketsDiscr
cbClTablePacketsDiscr.description: The Total Packets which were discarded to this client

cbClTableKBytesTxed.name: cbClTableKBytesTxed
cbClTableKBytesTxed.description: The Total KBytes transmitted to this client.

cbNetGatewayMngIP.name: cbNetGatewayMngIP
cbNetGatewayMngIP.description: C&M IP Address. Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbNetGatewayMngSubnetMask.name: cbNetGatewayMngSubnetMask
cbNetGatewayMngSubnetMask.description: C&M subnet mask. Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbNetDefaultGateway.name: cbNetDefaultGateway
cbNetDefaultGateway.description: The default gateway IP Address. The term gateway here, is reffering to another station in the same LAN of the CATV-Gateway. All IP packets that the CATV-Gateway is sending to the LAN (and not over the viedo) and their IP Address do not belong to the CATV-Gateway local ring will be sent to this gateway station unless cbNetDefaultGateway is 0.0.0.0 Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbNetPromiscuous.name: cbNetPromiscuous
cbNetPromiscuous.description: Enables/Disables Promiscuous Mode. Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbNetDualNIC.name: cbNetDualNIC
cbNetDualNIC.description: Enables/Disables Transportation NIC Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbNetGatewayDataIP.name: cbNetGatewayDataIP
cbNetGatewayDataIP.description: Transportation IP Address. Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbNetGatewayDataSubnetMask.name: cbNetGatewayDataSubnetMask
cbNetGatewayDataSubnetMask.description: Transportation subnet mask. Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbStuffingMode.name: cbStuffingMode
cbStuffingMode.description: Stuffing mode: either FF stuffing or Adaptation field stuffing

cbMpeMode.name: cbMpeMode
cbMpeMode.description: MPE mode: Packed MPE mode or Not packed MPE mode.

cbDVBClockPolarity.name: cbDVBClockPolarity
cbDVBClockPolarity.description: DVB Clock Polarity. (read only value - may be changed in CFG.INI only).

cbGatewaySWReset.name: cbGatewaySWReset
cbGatewaySWReset.description: CAUTION: Setting this param to cbTrue cause a S/W reset of the gateway.

cbTraceMask.name: cbTraceMask
cbTraceMask.description: Mask to select elements for trace.

cbTraceLevel.name: cbTraceLevel
cbTraceLevel.description: Trace level for elements specified by cbTraceMask

cbPktEncrypt.name: cbPktEncrypt
cbPktEncrypt.description: Enable/Disable encryption of the the transmitted packets. If cbPktEncrypt==cbTrue, packets will be encrypted only if cbClEncrEnable==cbTrue for that client.

cbGatewayDescription.name: cbGatewayDescription
cbGatewayDescription.description: A general description of this gateway. The description may be changed as needed.

cbApplicationFileName.name: cbApplicationFileName
cbApplicationFileName.description: TV Gateway Application Software File Name. Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbDataMappingMode.name: cbDataMappingMode
cbDataMappingMode.description: Data Boradcast Mode - Encodding mode of data from network.

cbMaxAllowableDelay.name: cbMaxAllowableDelay
cbMaxAllowableDelay.description: The Maximum allowable time (in mSec) which a packet can be delayed in the gateway.

cbQOSMode.name: cbQOSMode
cbQOSMode.description: Permissive mode will allow transmit to users obove their maximum rate when when band-width is available. Restrictive mode will not transmit any data to users above their maximum rate even if band-width is available.

cbQOSActive.name: cbQOSActive
cbQOSActive.description: Turn on (cbTrue) or off (cbFalse) the Quality of Service mechanism. When Quality of Service is turned off, the minimum CIR promised to users is ignored and data is transffered to users in the order it is received from the Ethernet by the gateway.

cbFPGAFileName.name: cbFPGAFileName
cbFPGAFileName.description: A string that holds the MCS file name loaded to the Gateway's Encoder. Changing this parameter will affect after system reset.

cbGrTable.name: cbGrTable
cbGrTable.description: This table contains the Groups definitions.

cbGrTableMinRate.name: cbGrTableMinRate
cbGrTableMinRate.description: The Group Minimum rate. This parameter affects only if QosMode=Global

cbGrTableMaxRate.name: cbGrTableMaxRate
cbGrTableMaxRate.description: The Group Maximum rate. This parameter affects only if QosMode=Global

cbStaticUserTable.name: cbStaticUserTable
cbStaticUserTable.description: This table contains the all the static users.

cbStaticUserEntry.name: cbStaticUserEntry
cbStaticUserEntry.description: Information about a particular static user.

cbStaticUserMAC.name: cbStaticUserMAC
cbStaticUserMAC.description: The group in which the static user resides.

cbMulticastTable.name: cbMulticastTable
cbMulticastTable.description: This table contains the all the multicasts.

cbMulticastSID.name: cbMulticastSID
cbMulticastSID.description: The group in which the multicast resides.

cbCfgClTable.name: cbCfgClTable
cbCfgClTable.description: This table contains updated configuration of all clients known to the gateway.

cbCfgClTableNode.name: cbCfgClTableNode
cbCfgClTableNode.description: Information about a particular client configuration.

cbCfgClTableBy.name: cbCfgClTableBy
cbCfgClTableBy.description: By whom the client was added.

cbTime.name: cbTime
cbTime.description: A string in the form HH:MM:SS that represents the gateway idea of the current time. Single digits should be preceeded by 0. Examples: 12:35:27 01:50:00 09:01:59

cbDate.name: cbDate
cbDate.description: A string representing the gateway idea of the current date. In order to set a different date, use the following format: <Full Month Name> <1 or 2 Digits of Day of Month>,<4 Digits of Year> Examples: September 1,1998 Januray 12, 2002

cbClientsInfoReset.name: cbClientsInfoReset
cbClientsInfoReset.description: This parameter is applicable only for clients that were NOT added by the CCU. The gateway will delete from its lists clients information (statistics and encryption parameters) for each client registered in the system for more then cbTClientsInfoReset seconds. cbTClientsInfoReset must be greater then 0.

cbCCU1.name: cbCCU1
cbCCU1.description: IP of CCU Server #1 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #1)

cbCCU2.name: cbCCU2
cbCCU2.description: IP of CCU Server #2 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #2)

cbCCU3.name: cbCCU3
cbCCU3.description: IP of CCU Server #3 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #3)

cbCCU4.name: cbCCU4
cbCCU4.description: IP of CCU Server #4 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #4)

cbCCU5.name: cbCCU5
cbCCU5.description: IP of CCU Server #5 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #5)

cbCCU6.name: cbCCU6
cbCCU6.description: IP of CCU Server #6 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #6)

cbCCU7.name: cbCCU7
cbCCU7.description: IP of CCU Server #7 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #7)

cbCCU8.name: cbCCU8
cbCCU8.description: IP of CCU Server #8 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #8)

cbCCU9.name: cbCCU9
cbCCU9.description: IP of CCU Server #9 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #9)

cbCCU10.name: cbCCU10
cbCCU10.description: IP of CCU Server #10 (set to 0.0.0.0 to disable CCU #10)

cbTestTxType.name: cbTestTxType
cbTestTxType.description: READ/WRITE Test Transfer Type: cbTestTypeOnePacket - one packet, cbTestTypeLowSpeedCont - Low Speed Continuous. cbTestTypeHighSpeedCont - High Speed Continuous.

cbDiagTestTxActive.name: cbDiagTestTxActive
cbDiagTestTxActive.description: Set to 0 in order to stop Test Transfer. Set to non-0 in order to activate it. (in case cbTestTxType = 1, set to 0 and to non-zero in order to re-send the single test packet)

cbSWServerIP.name: cbSWServerIP
cbSWServerIP.description: The TFTP server IP address. The S/W file will be TFTPed from this station. Use 0.0.0.0 to load a different local file (without TFTP).

cbSWSourceFileName.name: cbSWSourceFileName
cbSWSourceFileName.description: The software file name and its optional path (relative to the TFTP server root definition) to be downloaded from the server. Example: catvgw.dat

cbSWTargetFileName.name: cbSWTargetFileName
cbSWTargetFileName.description: The S/W file name (without path) on the Gateway. Example: ram.abs WARNING: cbApplicationFileName (under cbGeneralParam) is the name of the running S/W. If cbSWTargetFileName is different from cbApplicationFileName, it will be just downloaded to the Gateway and not used until cbApplicationFileName will be changed (in CFG.INI) to be equal to cbSWTargetFileName.

cbSWDownloadStart.name: cbSWDownloadStart
cbSWDownloadStart.description: Set cbSWDownloadStart to cbTrue in order to start the S/W download process. Set cbSWDownloadStart to cbFalse to interrupt (and stop) S/W download in progress (when cbSWDownloadStatus = cbDownloadInProgress).

cbSWDownloadStatus.name: cbSWDownloadStatus
cbSWDownloadStatus.description: Status of SW Download: cbIdle - Download has not started yet or has comleted and gateway already restarted with new version (not an error). cbDownloadInProgress - Download is currently in progrees (not an error). cbERRORTFTPServernotFound - Cannot find a TFTP server in the specified IP address - check and correct cbSWServerIP. cbERRORFileNotFound - Cannot find the specified file - check and correct cbSWFileName. cbERRORNotaSWFile - The specified file is not a SW file - check and correct cbSWFileName. cbERRORBadChecksum - Bad checksum - try to download again. cbERRORCommunicationFailed - Communication with server failed - try to download again. cbDownloadAborted - Download aborted by SNMP manager (cbSWDownloadStart was set to cbFalse during download).

cbFPGASourceFileName.name: cbFPGASourceFileName
cbFPGASourceFileName.description: The FPGA file name and its optional path (relative to the TFTP server root definition) to be downloaded from the server. Example: FPGA.DAT

cbFPGATargetFileName.name: cbFPGATargetFileName
cbFPGATargetFileName.description: The FPGA file name (without path) on the Gateway. Example: FPGA.DAT

cbFPGADownloadStart.name: cbFPGADownloadStart
cbFPGADownloadStart.description: Set cbFPGADownloadStart to cbTrue in order to start the FPGA download process. Set cbFPGADownloadStart to cbFalse to interrupt (and stop) FPGA download in progress (when cbFPGADownloadStatus = cbDownloadInProgress).

cbFPGADownloadStatus.name: cbFPGADownloadStatus
cbFPGADownloadStatus.description: Status of FPGA Download: cbIdle - Download has not started yet or has comleted and gateway already restarted with new version (not an error). cbDownloadInProgress - Download is currently in progrees (not an error). cbERRORTFTPServernotFound - Cannot find a TFTP server in the specified IP address - check and correct cbSWServerIP. cbERRORFileNotFound - Cannot find the specified file - check and correct cbFPGAFileName. cbERRORNotaSWFile - The specified file is not a SW file - check and correct cbFPGAFileName. cbERRORBadChecksum - Bad checksum - try to download again. cbERRORCommunicationFailed - Communication with server failed - try to download again. cbDownloadAborted - Download aborted by SNMP manager (cbFPGADownloadStart was set to cbFalse during download).
